objects.name: Web shells in Digium Phones
objects.description: Recently, Unit 42 observed an operation that targets the Elastix system used in the Digium phones. The attacker implants a webshell to exfiltrate data, by downloading and executing additional payloads inside the victim's Digium phone software (a FreePBX module written in PHP). In terms of the timeline, the webshell appears to be correlated to the Remote Code Execution (RCE) vulnerability CVE-2021-45461 in the Rest Phone Apps (restapps) module.
